        <bioghist id="ref2">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>The Committee for Democratic Election Laws was formed in 1971 to coordinate non-partisan court challenges to discriminatory election laws across the country. It challenged a number of statutes such as Pennsylvania's restrictions on minority party candidates, Florida's ten cent filing fees, loyalty oaths in Illinois, and age requirements for candidates and voters.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection consists of court documents, including transcripts, motions and appeals, as well as brochures and other publicity material.</p>
